  "response": "The normal waist size for women can vary based on factors such as age, genetics, and overall body composition. However, in general, a healthy waist measurement for women is often considered to be:\n\n- Less than 35 inches (88 cm) for most adult women to reduce the risk of health issues related to obesity.\n\nThat said, it's important to consider that body shape and composition also play significant roles in health. It's always a good idea for individuals to consult with healthcare professionals for personalized assessments and advice.",
